UI\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\b0 \cf4 \cb3 Shorthand for User Interface. It\'92s everything you, the \'93user\'94, interact with!\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\b \cf2 \cb3 GUI\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\b0 \cf4 \cb3 Shorthand for Graphical User Interface. First created in the 1980\'92s at Xerox PARC.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\b \cf2 \cb3 Responsive\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\b0 \cf4 \cb3 Responsive design is a design method that accommodates for things such as screen size, the platform the user is one and what way a device is oriented. This applies to websites takes advantage of features the browser provides.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\b \cf2 \cb3 Native\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\b0 \cf4 \cb3 Native applications are local to your device and take advantage of the various applications your device such as the camera, bluetooth and GPS. When you hear the term "mobile app", people are most likely referring to a Native application.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\b \cf2 \cb3 Hybrid\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\b0 \cf4 \cb3 This is a mix of both the Responsive and Native experience. It uses features of both mobile and web, and you can often download them from the app store. Hybrid apps are usually developed faster than native apps.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\b \cf2 \cb3 Skeuomorphic design\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\b0 \cf4 \cb3 Taking elements from the real world and bringing them into the digital world so the user is readily familiar with something, or to help make it more intuitive.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\b \cf2 \cb3 Flat design\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\b0 \cf4 \cb3 Represent things in the digital world without having to make it look like physical things, while focusing on usability.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\b \cf2 \cb3 Flat 2.0\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\b0 \cf4 \cb3 Aims to find a middle ground, using the best aspects of Skeuomorphism and Flat design.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\b \cf2 \cb3 Mobbin 
\i (Tool)
\i0 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\b0 \cf4 \cb3 A tool created for collections of the latest and greatest mobile design patterns, where users can save down the designs for later review and perusal.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\b \cf2 \cb3 UI Designer\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\b0 \cf4 \cb3 The role of a UI Designer focuses mainly on building out digital user interfaces, but more specifically, focusing on information architecture - such as how elements are arranged on a page, why they are there and how clearly that is communicated to the user. UI designers bring it all together, making sure there is a consistent design narrative that runs throughout the company through the creation of style guides and design systems.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\b \cf2 \cb3 UX Designer\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\b0 \cf4 \cb3 UX Designers focus on the holistic experience, identifying a problem, what it will take to solve it, iterating & refining user flows and the overall user's journey to a delightful experience. They would produce artifacts such as: wireframes, user flows, sitemaps, user journeys and affinity maps.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\b \cf2 \cb3 Graphic Designer\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\b0 \cf4 \cb3 A graphic designer has its roots in the print industry such as working on magazines and posters. Much of what they did then is still done today - just in a digital format! Their job is very visual and they generally decide how things are going to look. They make icons, choose colors, patterns and font pairings.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\b \cf2 \cb3 Principles of interaction design\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\b0 \cf4 \cb3 Bruce Tognazzini designed the first computer interface in the late 70's at Apple, and also created a list of 21 first principles of interaction to make for more effective interface design. In the lesson, we focused on four key principles: Levels of Consistency, Discoverability, Readability and Simplicity.\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0
\b\fs28 \cf4 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Levels of Consistency
\b0\fs32 \cb1 \
\pard\tx940\tx1440\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-1440\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl1\cf4 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Keep a consistent look and feel from screen to screen, as well as standardizing the location of certain items like menu bars.\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0
\b\fs28 \cf4 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Discoverability
\b0\fs32 \cb1 \
\pard\tx940\tx1440\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-1440\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl1\cf4 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Making sure that items that are important for a user to complete a task are visible, discoverable and accessible when they need them. User testing can help greatly with this.\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0
\b\fs28 \cf4 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Readability
\b0\fs32 \cb1 \
\pard\tx940\tx1440\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-1440\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl1\cf4 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Text should be high contrast, in a large enough size to be readable on the user\'92s device of choice, and key words should be first in menu items.\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0
\b\fs28 \cf4 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Simplicity
\b0\fs32 \cb1 \
\pard\tx940\tx1440\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-1440\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl1\cf4 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Making an interface easy to use without sacrificing essential user functions. Simplicity should be a benefit to the user. Complex items appear just in time for when a user needs them.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

