\b \cf2 \cb3 Typography\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\b0 \cf4 \cb3 Arranging text to make it more legible, readable and appealing. In the lesson, we discussed three of the parts of typography: Kerning, Leading and Font Pairings.\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0
\b\fs28 \cf4 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Kerning
\b0\fs32 \cb1 \
\pard\tx940\tx1440\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-1440\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl1\cf4 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Modifying space in between font characters, whether adding or taking away space.\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0
\b\fs28 \cf4 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Leading
\b0\fs32 \cb1 \
\pard\tx940\tx1440\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-1440\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl1\cf4 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Modifying space between lines of characters, either using or saving space on a page.\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0
\b\fs28 \cf4 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Font Pairings
\b0\fs32 \cb1 \
\pard\tx940\tx1440\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-1440\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl1\cf4 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
The art of combining different fonts or different styles of fonts from the same font family to create aesthetically beautiful looking typography.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\b \cf2 \cb3 Design systems\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\b0 \cf4 \cb3 A design system serves as a north star for a project, collecting all the aspects that enable a team to develop a design. It can grow and evolve over time with more assets & components.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\b \cf2 \cb3 Atomic design\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\b0 \cf4 \cb3 Inspired by basic units of matter in science, atomic design builds from small pieces into larger pieces. It is broken down into atoms, molecules, organisms, templates and pages, with each element building on the previous.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\b \cf2 \cb3 Navigation systems\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\b0 \cf4 \cb3 Navigation allows users to intuitively interact with the product and move through the interface you've designed. There are various navigation patterns that exist and which one you use depends on what you are building and who you are building for. Some common ones are: Hamburger menus, mega menus, call to action buttons, and breadcrumbs.\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl0
\b\fs28 \cf4 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Hamburger Menus
\b0\fs32 \cb1 \
\pard\tx940\tx1440\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-1440\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl1\cf4 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Hamburger menus are like those used at the top left of the Udacity classroom - a set of horizontal bars, like a hamburger, that hide or show a menu when clicked. These can helpfully be activated when needed, but can also potentially hide important menu items from the user.\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl0
\b\fs28 \cf4 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Mega Menus
\b0\fs32 \cb1 \
\pard\tx940\tx1440\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-1440\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl1\cf4 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Mega menus are larger menus that often come as dropdowns from a button or menu bar. They are robust and can hold a lot of menu items, but can also be too overloaded for the user.\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl0
\b\fs28 \cf4 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Call to Action buttons
\b0\fs32 \cb1 \
\pard\tx940\tx1440\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-1440\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl1\cf4 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Call to Action buttons tell the user to take action in some way, such as signing up for a free trial or a premium option. It can focus the user on one clear goal, but can also go wrong with poor copyrighting.\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl0
\b\fs28 \cf4 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Breadcrumbs
\b0\fs32 \cb1 \
\pard\tx940\tx1440\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-1440\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl1\cf4 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Breadcrumbs deal with website hierarchy, such as online shopping websites drilling further and further down into subcategories. They help users know where they came from, but don\'92t work well for large menu sets.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\b \cf2 \cb3 Style guides\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\b0 \cf4 \cb3 A style guide is a part of a design system that focuses on elements such as: icons, color, typography, and graphics. It helps designers work better with developers by providing them what they need to implement what you've created in a way that is true to what you've designed. Design systems can vary from product to product and can be very extensive, or be incredibly simplistic.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

